async def inline_query_handler(update: Update, context: ContextTypes.DEFAULT_TYPE):
    query = update.inline_query.query.strip()
    user_id = update.inline_query.from_user.id

    try:
        amount = int(query.replace("u", "").replace("-", "-"))

        if amount > 0 and user_balances.get(user_id, 0) < amount:
            await update.inline_query.answer([], switch_pm_text="‚ö†Ô∏èUSDT‰ΩôÈ¢ù‰∏çË∂≥", switch_pm_parameter="start", cache_time=0)
            return

        title = f"üí∞ ËΩ¨Ë¥¶Áªô‰Ω† {abs(amount)} USDT"
        msg_text = f"üí∞ ËΩ¨Ë¥¶Áªô‰Ω†  {abs(amount)} USDT\n\nËØ∑Âú®24Â∞èÊó∂ÂÜÖÈ¢ÜÂèñ"
        from_id = user_id

        transfer_key = f"{from_id}:{amount}"
        pending_transfers[transfer_key] = True
        user_balances[user_id] = user_balances.get(user_id, 0) - abs(amount)

        keyboard = [
            [InlineKeyboardButton("üì•Êî∂Ê¨æ", callback_data=f"claim:{from_id}:{amount}")]
        ]

        results = [
            InlineQueryResultArticle(
                id=str(uuid.uuid4()),
                title=title,
                input_message_content=InputTextMessageContent(msg_text),
                reply_markup=InlineKeyboardMarkup(keyboard)
            )
        ]

        await update.inline_query.answer(results, cache_time=0)
    except:
        await update.inline_query.answer([], switch_pm_text="‚ö†Ô∏èÊú™Áü•ÂëΩ‰ª§", switch_pm_parameter="start", cache_time=0)

def generate_tron_address_from_pool():
    path = "tron_addresses.json"
    if not os.path.exists(path):
        return None

    with open(path, "r") as f:
        pool = json.load(f)

    for item in pool:
        if not item.get("used"):
            item["used"] = True
            with open(path, "w") as f:
                json.dump(pool, f, indent=2)
            return item["address"]

    return None  # Ê≤°ÊúâÂèØÁî®Âú∞ÂùÄ
